After a devastating year, we all hope 2021 will be one of recovery. Businesses around the world have been battered by the Covid-19 pandemic, which cast a dark cloud on economies globally.
Indeed, the 37-member Organization for Economic Co-operation and Development (OECD) said in its December outlook that global output will return to pre-pandemic levels by the end of 2021 after witnessing a 4.2 per cent decline this year.



